Applying Colors and Backgrounds in CSS
CSS offers various ways to apply colors and backgrounds to HTML elements.

Colors
Hexadecimal Color Codes: Use a six-digit code starting with #. Each pair of digits represents the red, green, and blue values in hexadecimal format.
Example: #FF0000 (red)
RGB Color Codes: Use the rgb() function with three comma-separated values representing the red, green, and blue components in the range of 0 to 255.
Example: rgb(255, 0, 0) (red)
HSL Color Codes: Use the hsl() function with three comma-separated values representing the hue, saturation, and lightness.
Example: hsl(0, 100%, 50%) (red)
Backgrounds
Solid Color: Use the background-color property with a color value.
Gradient: Use the background-image property with the linear-gradient() or radial-gradient() function to create gradients.
Image: Use the background-image property with a URL to an image.
Example
HTML
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Color and Background Example</title>
    <style>
        .hex-color {
            background-color: #FFB6C1;
        }

        .rgb-color {
            background-color: rgb(0, 128, 0);
        }

        .hsl-color {
            background-color: hsl(240, 100%, 50%);
        }

        .gradient {
            background-image: linear-gradient(to right, #f06b6b, #f7f298);
        }

        .image-background {
            background-image: url("path/to/your/image.jpg");
            background-size: cover;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="hex-color">Hex Color</div>
    <div class="rgb-color">RGB Color</div>
    <div class="hsl-color">HSL Color</div>
    <div class="gradient">Gradient</div>
    <div class="image-background">Image Background</div>
</body>
</html>
Use code with caution.

Explanation
Hex Color: The hex-color div uses a hexadecimal color code.
RGB Color: The rgb-color div uses RGB color codes.
HSL Color: The hsl-color div uses HSL color codes.
Gradient: The gradient div uses a linear gradient with two color stops.
Image Background: The image-background div uses an image as the background and sets the background-size to cover to ensure the image fills the entire div.
This example demonstrates how to apply various colors and backgrounds to HTML elements using CSS. You can experiment with different color values and background properties to achieve the desired visual effects for your web pages.